    "body": "**Actionable comments posted: 4**\n\n<details>\n<summary>🧹 Nitpick comments (1)</summary><blockquote>\n\n<details>\n<summary>src/components/Dashboard.tsx (1)</summary><blockquote>\n\n`447-458`: **Consider adding keyboard accessibility for the range slider.**\n\nThe slider correctly uses `onMouseUp` and `onTouchEnd` for debounced API updates, but keyboard users adjusting the slider with arrow keys won't trigger these events. Consider adding `onKeyUp` or `onBlur` to persist changes made via keyboard navigation.\n\nAdditionally, adding `aria-label` would improve screen reader support.\n\n<details>\n<summary>♿ Suggested accessibility improvements</summary>\n\n```diff\n <input \n   type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max={g.targetAmount} step=\"10\" value={g.currentAmount}\n+  aria-label={`Progress for ${g.name}`}\n   onChange={(e) => {\n     const val = parseFloat(e.target.value);\n     setGoals(prev => prev.map(goal => \n       goal.id === g.id ? { ...goal, currentAmount: val } : goal\n     ));\n   }}\n   onMouseUp={(e) => handleUpdateGoalProgress(g.id, parseFloat((e.target as HTMLInputElement).value))}\n   onTouchEnd={(e) => handleUpdateGoalProgress(g.id, parseFloat((e.target as HTMLInputElement).value))}\n+  onKeyUp={(e) => handleUpdateGoalProgress(g.id, parseFloat((e.target as HTMLInputElement).value))}\n   className=\"w-full h-1.5 bg-gray-200 rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer accent-teal-600\"\n />\n```\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nIn `@src/components/Dashboard.tsx` around lines 447 - 458, The range input\ncurrently updates state via setGoals and only persists via onMouseUp/onTouchEnd\nwhich misses keyboard users; add a keyboard/blur handler (e.g., onKeyUp and/or\nonBlur) that calls handleUpdateGoalProgress(g.id, parseFloat((e.target as\nHTMLInputElement).value)) to persist changes made with arrow keys, and add an\naccessible label (aria-label or aria-labelledby) to the input so screen readers\ncan describe the slider; reference the existing handlers and state update\n(setGoals, handleUpdateGoalProgress, g.id, g.currentAmount) when making the\nchange.\n```\n\n</details>\n\n</blockquote></details>\n\n</blockquote></details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for all review comments with AI agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nInline comments:\nIn `@src/app/api/goals/route.ts`:\n- Around line 43-52: The PATCH handler currently calls parseFloat(currentAmount)\nwithout validating it first; update the handler that reads { id, currentAmount }\nto parse and validate currentAmount (e.g., let amount =\nparseFloat(currentAmount); ensure Number.isFinite(amount) and amount >= 0) and\nreturn a 400 JSON error if validation fails, then use that validated amount in\nprisma.goal.updateMany (referencing id, session.user.id and currentAmount ->\namount) to prevent NaN or negative updates.\n- Around line 27-35: Validate and sanitize parsed numeric inputs before calling\nprisma.goal.create: parse targetAmount and currentAmount using parseFloat (or\nNumber) into local variables, check Number.isFinite(parsed) and that values are\n>= 0, and if invalid either default to 0 (for currentAmount) or return a 400\nerror for targetAmount; then pass those sanitized numeric variables into the\ndata object used by prisma.goal.create (referencing targetAmount and\ncurrentAmount from the sanitized variables rather than parsing inline).\n\nIn `@src/components/Dashboard.tsx`:\n- Around line 183-190: The PATCH handler handleUpdateGoalProgress currently\nignores failures which can leave optimistic local state (goals) stale; modify\nhandleUpdateGoalProgress to detect non-ok responses and on failure either call\nfetchData() to re-sync the UI with server state or trigger a user-visible error\n(e.g., toast/notification) and then call fetchData() to restore correct values;\nensure you reference the same fetch to \"/api/goals\" and the fetchData function\nso the UI is refreshed when res.ok is false or when a network/error is thrown.\n- Line 59: The Dashboard component declares a prop userName that is never used;\neither remove the unused prop from the Dashboard function signature (remove the\n{ userName }: { userName: string } parameter and its type) and update any\ncallers that pass userName, or use the prop inside the component’s render output\nby adding a greeting or display element that references userName within the\nDashboard JSX; locate the Dashboard function declaration to apply one of these\nfixes and update any callers accordingly.\n\n---\n\nNitpick comments:\nIn `@src/components/Dashboard.tsx`:\n- Around line 447-458: The range input currently updates state via setGoals and\nonly persists via onMouseUp/onTouchEnd which misses keyboard users; add a\nkeyboard/blur handler (e.g., onKeyUp and/or onBlur) that calls\nhandleUpdateGoalProgress(g.id, parseFloat((e.target as HTMLInputElement).value))\nto persist changes made with arrow keys, and add an accessible label (aria-label\nor aria-labelledby) to the input so screen readers can describe the slider;\nreference the existing handlers and state update (setGoals,\nhandleUpdateGoalProgress, g.id, g.currentAmount) when making the change.\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🪄 Autofix (Beta)</summary>\n\nFix all unresolved CodeRabbit comments on this PR:\n\n- [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"4b0d0e0a-96d7-4f10-b296-3a18ea78f0b9\"} --> Push a commit to this branch (recommended)\n- [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"ff5b1114-7d8c-49e6-8ac1-43f82af23a33\"} --> Create a new PR with the fixes\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details>\n<summary>ℹ️ Review info</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⚙️ Run configuration</summary>\n\n**Configuration used**: Path: .coderabbit.yaml\n\n**Review profile**: CHILL\n\n**Plan**: Pro\n\n**Run ID**: `a97e8b90-246a-49fb-bb43-d4b9c899da77`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📥 Commits</summary>\n\nReviewing files that changed from the base of the PR and between 17a599dcfd316b10936ddcef1fa48b495e2728b5 and 5c78cf4d00617f47cebc9958be060b3769155276.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📒 Files selected for processing (3)</summary>\n\n* `prisma/schema.prisma`\n* `src/app/api/goals/route.ts`\n* `src/components/Dashboard.tsx`\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit for review status -->",
